Duties and Responsibilities
Develops advanced Excel forecast models incorporating extensive programmatic functionality (VBA);
Ensures the forecast models meet the business and technical requirements laid out by the stakeholders;
Uses business logic, recognizes client needs and possesses very strong Excel skills to create forecast models based on best practice methodologies;
Quality checks completed models for adherence to specified business logic, calculation errors, and formatting;
Remains current with technologies and best practices within the development space, as well as disseminating new best practices to other team members;
Mentors other forecast model developers on the team and ensuring appropriate development practices are followed;
Participates in client briefings to understand the requirements;
Understands forecast models provided by clients for integration into i2e;
Interacts with cross-functional teams such as Data Integration, Model Development and Data Visualization teams in order to complete tasks/projects;
Participates in team meetings for aligning with team's daily and weekly goals;
Performs all tasks assigned by Manager, Forecasting/Team Lead.
