Reporting to Director, Risk Sharing Pool Management & Optimization, the Junior Data Scientist will be responsible for the risk selections and performance monitoring of the company's participation in the Risk Sharing Pool. The incumbent will be responsible for the execution and monitoring of strategic initiatives to drive and achieve our RSP financial objectives across the country for both the broker and direct channels. This role involves application of programming languages such as R and SQL on analyzing and solving business problems in a cross-functional collaboration setting.

KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES
Design, develop and enhance effective analytical solutions in collaboration with business stakeholders in streamlining and automating the RSP analytics, including but not limited to:
Thorough understanding of industry standards and practices for various usages of the pool across different jurisdictions,
Effective application of predictive analytics models and business judgements to measure each portfolio’s ceding potentials,
Evaluation of predictive analytics models in the use case of RSP and provide feedback and review as needed,
Active collaboration with various teams such as Modelling, Regional Pricing, Fraud, Technology, Claims, and Corporate Actuarial, to achieve our financial objectives;
Analyze and monitor the financial performance of pool usage. Provide analyses on financial projections and how results track against operation plans and against modelled outcomes;
Support the implementation team for productionizing changes to ceding logic;
Continually focus on innovation and process improvement to promote leading practices and efficiency across the organization in the context of RSP.
Coach and Review the work from Junior Data Analysts.
JOB REQUIREMENTS
University degree or higher in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Mathematics, or a related discipline;
2+ years of employment experience with statistical programming languages like Python and R, and database query languages like SQL;
Ability to work both independently and in collaboration with others;
Sound problem solving ability;
Clear verbal and written communications;
Knowledge or prior experience working with Property and Casualty insurance and/or risk sharing pool is a strong asset.
